  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. Key legal elements typically include:\n\n1. Concealing illegal financial transactions\n2. Disguising the source of criminal proceeds\n3. Transforming \"dirty\" money into seemingly \"clean\" money\n4. Intentionally hiding the nature, location, source, ownership, or control of funds\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary between jurisdictions, but most involve:\n- Intentional financial transactions\n- Proceeds from criminal activity\n- Attempts to make illegal funds appear legitimate\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal definitions?",
